Literally at the center of the world, Sicily lies tranquilly at the juncture of the West and the East. Officially a part of Italy, Sicily is the largest island in the Mediterranean. Due to its singular geographic position, Sicily has been witness to an influx of varying cultures, traditions and art. Remnants of the Roman and Greek Era are evident here with temples, piazzas and theaters built around the idea of the long buried ancient architecture. Not only does a trip to Sicily entail scenic amusements with volcanoes and sandy beaches, it bestows a chance to turn the years back and behold some of the oldest marvels in human history.